tldr: https://twitter.com/chrisachard/status/1175022111758442497?s=21

import React from "react"
import ReactDOM from "react-dom"
ReactDom.render(WHAT YOU WANT TO RENDER, WHERE TO RENDER IT)

e.g.
import React from 'react'
import ReactDom from 'react-dom'
ReactDOM.render(
  <ul>
    <li>1</li>
    <li>2</li>
    <li>3</li>
   </ul>,
  document.getElementById('root')
  )
  ///
  
---
- functions should use camel case and start with a capital letter
- instead of putting everything under the content to be rendered, we could make a function that returns it, then render the function
e.g.
function MyApp() {
  return (
    <ul>
      <li>1</li>
      <li>2</li>
      <li>3</li>
    </ul>
  )
 }

ReactDOM.render(
  <MyApp />,
  document.getElementById("root")
)
///

---
//React html & css prac
import React from "react"
import ReactDOM from "react-dom"

function MyInfo(){
  return(
  <div>
  <h1>Seasonal</h1>
  <p>Hi I'm learning React and making slow but steady progress!<p>
  <ol>
    <li>My bed</li>
    <li>My bed but with a cat on it<li>
    <li>See above</li>
  </ol>
  </div>
  )
}
ReactDOM.render(<MyInfo />, document.getElementById("root"))
///

From ES6: export default FileName
//where FileName is FileName.js
///

Remember to instantiate with <FileName />
///

To import a JS file: import FileName from "./FileName.js"
//where ./ means current, root folder and ./folder/FileName.js indicates it's inside folder
///

Appropriate naming is important! If creating a footer, the ELEMENT is called <footer></footer>.
But you can call the COMPONENT <BestFooter>
///



